{"key":"processedPost-11766002","value":{"id":11766002,"first":11764942,"last":11770392,"when":1262646614,"utime":"01/05/10 01:10 AM","content":"Verm will increase the performance of any bulk substrate substantially.&nbsp; You don't 'need' verm, nor do you 'need' gypsum, but both will pay far more in returns than their cost and extra effort.<br /><br />You don't want to leach your substrate by soaking in water.&nbsp; Simply hydrate to field capacity, and then load into jars or bags and drop into a pan of water that you then heat to boiling.&nbsp; Stick a meat thermometer into the center of the substrate, and time one hour from the time the center reaches 140F/60C.&nbsp; Try not to let the temperature exceed 160F/70C.<br />RR","title":"Re: Coir sub help"}}